  "description": [
    "Page Two flt Chpel Iffl Weekly LOUIS GRAVES Editor SUBSCSIPTION KATES Om T Six Moo K IAO Tta Moati TO lrdM fxMaAor t Ckafef Hill Nrtfc rmdn the act f Mtrd J 117 A New Trial for a Girl Out in the mountains in the southwest corner of Virginia a girl Edith Maxwell killed her father about a year ago and was put on trial for murder Testi mony was given and was not disputed that her father had in flicted upon her the most brutal treatment including severe beat ings Yet the jury brought in a verdict of guilty and she was sentenced to 25 years imprison ment In view of the facts that had been brought out about the bar barous conduct of the father it is no wonder that the outcome of the trial was thought by civi lized people all over the land to be an abominable miscarriage of justice The girls friends be gan at once an effort to obtain for her a new trial and they were aided by strangers whose sympathy had been aroused by the severity of the punishment The Virginia Supreme Cqprt of Appeals has granted the girl a new trial"
